<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000059#     1#       501.17#">Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-501.17</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_59.1-501.17"/><heading><desig>§ 59.1-501.17.</desig><title>Decision for court; legal consequences; reasonable time; reason to know</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>(a)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Whether a term is conspicuous or is unenforceable under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-501.5"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-501.5">§§ 59.1-501.5 (a)<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#        501.5#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or (b), 59.1-501.11, or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-502.9"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-502.9">§ 59.1-502.9 (a)<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#        502.9#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and whether an attribution procedure is commercially reasonable or effective under <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-501.8"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-501.8">§§ 59.1-501.8<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#        501.8#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-502.12"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-502.12">59.1-502.12<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#       502.12#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, or <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 59.1-502.13"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 59.1-502.13">§ 59.1-502.13<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000059#     1#       502.13#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> are questions to be determined by the court.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>(b)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Whether an agreement has legal consequences is determined by this chapter.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_c"/><heading><desig>(c)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Whenever this chapter requires any action to be taken within a reasonable time, what is a reasonable time for taking the action depends on the nature, purpose, and circumstances of the action. Any time that is not manifestly unreasonable may be fixed by agreement.</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_d"/><heading><desig>(d)</desig></heading><bodyText><p> A person has reason to know a fact if the person has knowledge of the fact or, from all the facts and circumstances known to the person without investigation, the person should be aware that the fact exists.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p><citation normalizedCite="2004 VA CH 794"><content><span normalizedCite="2004 Va. Ch. 794">2004, c. 794<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2004#000794#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PVD0-004G-K3WT-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="productContentSetIdentifier">10816</dc:source><dc:date dateType="last-updated">2016-06-15</dc:date></dc:metadata><publicationInfo><publicationName>CODE OF VIRGINIA </publicationName><copyright>Copyright © 2016  by Matthew Bender &amp; Company, Inc. a member of the LexisNexis Group. All rights reserved</copyright></publicationInfo><hierarchy><hierarchyLevel levelType="title"><heading><desig>TITLE 59.1.</desig><title>TRADE AND COMMERCE</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="chapter"><heading><desig>CHAPTER 43.</desig><title>UNIFORM COMPUTER INFORMATION TRANSACTIONS ACT</title></heading><hierarchyLevel levelType="part"><heading><desig>PART 1.</desig><title>GENERAL PROVISIONS</title></heading></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchyLevel></hierarchy><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Commercial Law (UCC)</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6QUI5QjdCNzBDNjY0NEY3QzlGRTNCQTMzQ0IwQ0MzRUQ7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem><className>Reasonable Time &amp; Seasonableness</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MDUzRDMzRTk2RDc0NDYxOEI3MkRGMUZFMjUzREQyNEQ7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6NUY1N0M2MTVDREQwNEE4NTk1OUMzMUQ0RkZBQkVBODg</classCode></classificationItem></classificationItem></classification><classificationGroup classificationScheme="indexing-terms"><classification classificationScheme="legal"><classificationItem><className>Business &amp; Corporate Compliance</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MUFEMUQ2QTA1OUZCNEE5RjkzNTA2RERFMUNEOTk1RTI7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD0</classCode><classificationItem score="90"><className>Antitrust</className><classCode>Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6REEyRTNDM0JGQzYyNEMyOEFGNTAwNUJEOUU1MDg4NjU7cGFyZW50Z3VpZD11cm46dG9waWM6MUFEMUQ2QTA1OUZCNEE5RjkzNTA2RERFMUNEOTk1RTI</classCode></classificationItem><classificationItem score="90"><className>Computer &amp; Intern